  object edDescription: TMemo
    Left = 10
    Height = 296
    Top = 224
    Width = 1157
    Color = clCream
    Font.Height = -15
    Lines.Strings = (
      'A conic is the curve obtained as the intersection of a plane with the surface of a double cone (a cone with two nappes). Beside the degenerate conics (so called, if the intersection is a point, a line or a pair of intersecting lines), there are 3 types of conics: the ellipse, parabola, and hyperbola, the circle being in fact a special kind of ellipse.'
      ''
      'The equations given are those for the conics put into standard forms in Cartesian coordinates, meaning that the conics are in a standard position:'
      ''
      'PARABOLA: Parabola with the focus on the x-axis, thus always passing through the origin (0, 0).'
      ''
      'CIRCLE: Circle with center (0, 0) and radius a.'
      ''
      'ELLIPSE: Ellipse with the center at the origin (0, 0) and the x-axis as principal axis. The vertices and the foci are on the x-axis. The major axis is defined as the chord between the two vertices, which is the longest chord of the ellipse (thus, you always have: a > b).'
      ''
      'HYPERBOLA: Hyperbola with the center at the origin (0, 0) and the x-axis as principal axis. The vertices and the foci are on the x-axis. As for the ellipse, the major axis is defined as the chord between the two vertices, but here it''s the shortest chord between the branches of the hyperbola.'
    )
    ParentFont = False
    ReadOnly = True
    TabOrder = 14
    TabStop = False
  end
